Cats experimentally infected with EIV demonstrated respiratory signs and virus shedding with transmission to other cats (

  29
 ). A strain of influenza discovered in a camel in Mongolia was directly related to a circulating equine H3N8 strain, but horizontal spread in camels could not be determined (

